name: VARIOUS BLANK PAGES
description: Produced with Doro Boehme, a fellow admirer of the book works of Ed Ruscha. Our work at the Joan Flasch Artists’ Book Collection at SAIC gives us the privilege of access to some of Ruscha’s most famous and rare book works such as Twentysix Gasoline Stations and Nine Swimming Pools, as well as insight to the glut of knock-offs and homages that the scene produces. We chose to merge these phenomena while looking at another: Ruscha’s love of empty space. Various Blank Pages consists of reproductions of the blank pages from Ruscha’s iconic books. Scanned directly from the original works and designed to look like one of his, perhaps the best part about this book is its alternate function as a notebook should the novelty of the piece ever fade. 66 pages, 6”x8”, offset printed and perfect bound.

name: The Musicians LP by Brain Vacation
description: The first release from Wall of Youth Records! WOY001! Brain Vacation’s vinyl debut! A punk rock masterpiece 13 billion years in the making. 10 songs at 33.33 RPM. Listen and download for free at brainvacation.info. The LP is pressed on severely heavy 180 gram “molten core” colored vinyl and housed in a 12”x12” 3-color matte jacket with 2-sided lyric sheet/insert, shrink-wrapped for posterity and limited to 250 copies. Release date: February 26, 2013. (Layout, design, and drumming by Eric Baskauskas, whose store you are currently browsing.)

name: OVER TIME
description:
DEATH BY PIZZA!

22 pages, printed on demand and bound in a printed hardcover. Your order will be shipped directly from Shutterfly (see shutterfly.com), fresh off the presses. Measures 8"x8" closed.

Domestic shipping is included in the price.

name: LIMITED EDITION Prints
description: I used an electric sander to remove all the paint from the exterior of my 1994 Nissan Sentra Limited Edition. I saved the dust that came from the car during the sanding and mixed it with oil to make ink. I used all of the ink to make as many prints as I could. I got 243. Each "Limited Edition" dust-print comes with two others: 1) A field of Dupli-Color Hot Rod Gray, which is the paint I used on the car after stripping the paint 2) A short text page detailing the process and its results. Produced in 2010. The paint-dust and text prints were made on a Vandercook letterpress. Each print is 19" x 12.5" and is signed by the artist. For a full description of the project, including many more images, please visit ericbaskauskas.info/LE

name: LIMITED EDITION Prints [USED CAR SALE!]
description: CERTIFIED USED ART! FREE SHIPPING! These prints are exactly the same as the brand-new prints, except they've got a few extra miles on them. From September 2 through November 14, 2010, they were displayed in a Chicago storefront as part of the Pop-Up Art Loop program. As a product of their being on display, the prints all exhibit signs of wear. A few bear holes from pins, a few have grease spots from hanging putty, etc. None of these blemishes are enough to diminish the visual quality of the work, and at almost half price, it's hard to resist. Own a piece of history!
